gap opening within the $C_2T$\nstripe state. Although the nodes at the Fermi energy are locally stable, they\ncan be annihilated after braiding with other nodes connecting them to adjacent\n(folded) bands. Therefore, if the translation symmetry is broken, the gap at\none particle per unit cell can open even if the system preserves the $C_2T$ and\nvalley $U(1)$ symmetries, and the gap to remote bands remains open.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 24 Feb 2020 16:41:23 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 8 May 2020 16:54:40 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 13 Jul 2020 12:37:06 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-08-05"}
