-to-noise ratio. Other strong\nlines such as H$\\alpha$, CaII IRT, the MgI triplet region, and KI D1 are\nanalysed, and are also consistent with the modelled effects, without\nconsidering any contribution from the exoplanet atmosphere. Thus, the\ntransmission spectrum reveals no detectableNaI absorption in HD 209458b. We\ndiscuss how previous pioneering studies of this benchmark object may have\noverlooked these effects. While for some star-planet systems these effects are\nsmall, for other planetary atmospheres the results reported in the literature\nmay require revision.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 24 Feb 2020 23:57:18 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-04-08"}
